Sentencas: To attain superior electrochemical performance, a new series of high-entropy double perovskites are investigated as cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Novel high entropy double pervoskite cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In this study, three PrBa0.5Sr0.5Co1.5Fe0.5O5 double perovskites with different dopings of La, Pr, Sm, Gd, Nd, Y elements in A-site, high-entropy oxides (HEOs) cathodes are successfully prepared by EDTA-citrate combustion method and used as potential cathodes for SOFC at intermediate temperature.
Titulo: Novel high entropy double pervoskite cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Three HEOs cathodes all form single phase double perovskite structure and match chemically well with Gd0.2Ce0.8O2-delta(GDC) electrolyte.
Titulo: Novel high entropy double pervoskite cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Linear thermal expansion coefficient of (La0.2Pr0.2Sm0.2Gd0.2Nd0.2) Ba0.5Sr0.5Co1.5Fe0.5O5(LPSGNBSCF) at 200-1000 degrees C range is found to be moderate, 18.39 x 10-6 K-1.
Titulo: Novel high entropy double pervoskite cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Typical anode supported SOFC with LPSGNBSCF cathode exhibits an excellent output performance of 1000 mW cm-2 with a lower polarization resistance of 0.3 omega cm2 at 800 degrees C. These results might suggest that LPSGNBSCF can be a potential excellent cathode for SOFC.
Titulo: Novel high entropy double pervoskite cathode for solid oxide fuel cells
